                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="arkroyal_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a British <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/aircraft-carrier" title="aircraft carrier definition"><span class="ndv">aircraft carrier</span></a> <span class="gloss" hclass="gloss" htag="span">(= a large ship with an area where aircraft can take off and land)</span>. There is a tradition in the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-royal-navy#the_royal_navy_topg_1" title="Royal Navy definition"><span class="ndv">Royal Navy</span></a> of naming important ships <span class="ebi">Ark Royal.</span> The first one was a ship that fought the Spanish <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/armada#armada_sng_1" title="Armada definition"><span class="ndv">Armada</span></a>. Another famous <span class="ebi">Ark Royal</span> was sunk in the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-second-world-war" title="Second World War definition"><span class="ndv">Second World War</span></a>.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
